channel.title: Error Message Upon Compiling
channel.description:
Hope this isn't a double post, I just wasn't getting any replies since I rudely wedged it in ruler's thread.
Anyway, when I try to compile the extracted, updated Aryan375b with scripts included, I get a message saying this:
[img]http://www.mypicturespace.com/uploads/d9e288f04a.jpg[/img]
I've tried various things to no avail. It was suggested that I didn't have an environment variable for Java, but that isn't the case. It was also suggested my scripts were busted, yet that should not affect my ability to run the client.
For you guys who are helping me get well-rooted in all this, I can assure you I will eventually be helping others once I obtain the know how!
Cheers.[br][size=1]Posted at: April 24, 2006, 03:32:07 pm[/size][hr]Update: I've abandoned the version posted by ruler for shits and giggles. Well, I went to the version offered on the thread for Mopar's autoupdater and attempted to compile, now getting this message:
[url=http://www.mypicturespace.com][img]http://www.mypicturespace.com/uploads/4260a20c72.jpg[/img][/url]
I would give my left testicle to resolve this crap. Forceps, anyone?
